# Codeband environment variables
#
# ── Claude authentication ───────────────────────────────────────
# Used by every Claude-based agent (Conductor, Planner, Coders,
# Reviewers, Mergemaster) and the cb prs/issues --smart helpers.
#
# Codeband resolves Claude auth in this order at startup:
#   1. CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN env var (from `claude setup-token`)
#   2. Host subscription OAuth, picked up automatically:
#        macOS: Keychain entry from `claude` login
#        Linux/Windows: $CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR/.credentials.json
#        (default ~/.claude/.credentials.json)
#   3. ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (last-resort pay-per-token)
# Codeband auto-strips ANTHROPIC_API_KEY when (1) or (2) is present,
# so the subscription path wins and you don't silently burn API credits.
#
# Option A: Anthropic API key — pay-per-token, no subscription caps.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# Option B: long-lived Claude OAuth token — required for Docker/CI
# where the host keychain isn't accessible. Generate with:
#   claude setup-token
# CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=...
# (Option C — no env var — works on your own host if you've run
# `claude` login: Codeband will detect and use the subscription
# automatically.)
#
# ── Codex authentication (optional, for Codex agents) ───────────
# Unlike Claude, Codex is API-KEY-FIRST by default: when both are
# present, OPENAI_API_KEY wins. Rationale: parallel Codex workers
# can exhaust a ChatGPT subscription's quota quickly, and OpenAI's
# own docs recommend API keys for automation.
#
# Either set OPENAI_API_KEY below, or run `codex login --device-auth`
# on the host (works locally and in Docker — your ~/.codex is mounted
# into containers). If you don't use Codex agents, leave this unset.
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
#
# ── Platform & GitHub ───────────────────────────────────────────
BAND_API_KEY=band_u_...
GH_TOKEN=ghp_...
#
# ── Memory backend override (optional) ──────────────────────────
# Codeband auto-detects Band.ai memory availability at startup.
# Set this to force a specific backend (useful for CI or debugging).
# BAND_MEMORY_MODE=auto   # auto (default) | band | local
